Scientists consider the American bullfrog one of the world’s top 100 invasive species. It was introduced by the food industry for the culinary delicacy many find in frog legs. Now it's eating everything in sight in Northern California ponds. http://www.sacbee.com/news/local/environment/article195771914.html …
